                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Talbotton, Ga.</placeName>
                                        <date>Sept. 27. 1852</date>
                              </p>
                              <p><addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser Esq.</addressee>!</p>
                              <p>Dear Sir!</p>
                              <p>We the undersigned chosen officer's of the hebrew<lb/> benevolent
                                        society of <placeName>Talbotton Ga.</placeName> are
                                        taking<lb/> the liberty to inform you of the following
                                        resolutions <sic>wich</sic> have been <sic>past</sic> by a
                                        majority<lb/> of the members of said society at their
                                        last<lb/> meeting held at the <date>18</date> inst.
                                        requesting you to<lb/> insert the same in the next Occident
                                        for <sic>wich</sic> you<lb/> will please forward your
                                        account for payment<lb/> to this place.</p>
                              <p>Resolved, that all the money <sic>wich</sic> is in
                                                  <sic>posession</sic> of<lb/> the hebrew benevolent
                                        society of this place<lb/>
                                        <sic>wich</sic> amounts to fifty Dollars shall be
                                        apropi<lb/>ated to buy a <sic>silvre</sic> ornament for a
                                        sefer Torah<lb/> in <sic>wich</sic> all the names of the
                                        members shall be<lb/> engraved.</p>
                              <p>Resolved, that the same shall be presented to the newly<lb/>
                                        <sic>build</sic> congregation <del>of</del> in the of
                                                  <placeName>Williamsburgh</placeName><lb/> state of
                                                  <placeName>New-York</placeName>.</p>
                              <p>Resolved, that <persName>Mr. Moses Selig</persName> is chosen to
                                        present<lb/> the same after its completion to the
                                        President<lb/> of said congregation in the month of
                                                  <date><sic>february</sic></date><lb/> next.</p>
                              <p>Resolved, that the forgoing resolutions shall be printed<lb/> in
                                        the next Occident.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)"><persName>Morris Selz</persName>. Pres.</p>
                              <p><persName role="author">Abraham Cahn</persName>, Sec.</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>Following are the names of the members of the<lb/> society:</p>
                              <list type="simple">
                                        <head/>
                                        <item>
                                                  <persName>Morris Selz</persName>
                                        </item>
                                        <item>
                                                  <persName>Moses Selig</persName>
                                        </item>
                                        <item>
                                                  <persName>Gabriel Selig</persName>
                                        </item>
                                        <item>
                                                  <persName>Samuel Straus</persName>
                                        </item>
                                        <item>
                                                  <persName>Leopold Straus</persName>
                                        </item>
                                        <item>
                                                  <persName>Meyer Kayser</persName>
                                        </item>
                                        <item>
                                                  <persName role="author">Abraham Kahn</persName>
                                        </item>
                                        <item>
                                                  <persName>Solomon Meyer</persName>
                                        </item>
                              </list>
                              <p>Should any thing be incorrect in this lines in the<lb/> way of
                                        spelling or any other way we beg you<lb/> to correct if for
                                        we are all inexperienced hands.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(6)">Respectfully</p>
                              <p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Abr. Cahn</persName>
                                        sec.</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>371 <sic>Wallnut</sic> Str.</placeName>
                              </p>
